-- South Africa's Manuel to brief media on IMF post
-- 
-- Fri Jun 10, 2011 6:52am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/06/10/us-safrica-imf-idUSTRE7591WR20110610

 

 JOHANNESBURG  (Reuters) - South Africa's Trevor Manuel will brief the media at 7 a.m. EDT on Friday concerning speculation he might join the race to head the IMF, the Presidency said in a statement. 

 "Minister Manuel would like to engage the media regarding the IMF position of MD (managing director)," the brief statement said. It gave no further details. (Reporting by  Stella Mapenzauswa , Editing by Ed Cropley)